<p class="newssubhead_t1">Women in Ag workshop planned for April 1</p>
<p>Iowa Women in Agriculture is hosting a one-day regional workshop in Mount Pleasant on April 1. Sessions will focus on financial management, marketing, online marketing, estate planning, long-term care insurance and wind energy.</p>
<p>&quot;The regional meetings are designed to provide women involved in agriculture with opportunities to learn from presenters and to network with each other,&quot; said Angie Treptow, president of Iowa Women in Agriculture.</p>
<p>The workshop will be held at the Iowa Wesleyan College library, 107 Broad St. Registration begins at 9 a.m., with workshop sessions scheduled from 9:30 to 3:30 p.m. Lunch is included.</p>
<p>Contact Rhonda Harness by Thursday at (563) 332-1744 for a $30 registration fee. Registration is $40 after that. Payments can be made at the door.</p>
<p><font style="background-color:#E6EEFF">Workshop sponsors include the U.S. Department of Agriculture; state of Iowa; Rain and Hail Agricultural Insurance; DTN; Farm Credit Services of America; Farm Bureau Financial Services; Successful Farming; Monsanto; Channel Bio Corp.; Stine Seed Co.; and Pioneer.</font></p>
